    <h1>Gluten-Free Substitute for Cream of Celery Soup</h1>
    <p>For those who follow a gluten-free diet, finding suitable substitutes for common pantry staples can be a challenge. One such staple is cream of celery soup, which is often used as a base in casseroles, soups, and other dishes. Unfortunately, many store-bought versions contain gluten, making them unsuitable for those with celiac disease or gluten sensitivity. In this article, we’ll explore how to create a delicious and gluten-free cream of celery soup substitute that you can use in your favorite recipes.</p>

    <h2>Why Go Gluten-Free?</h2>
    <p>Gluten is a protein found in wheat, barley, and rye. For individuals with celiac disease, consuming gluten can lead to severe digestive issues, nutrient deficiencies, and long-term health complications. Even for those without celiac disease, gluten sensitivity can cause discomfort, bloating, and fatigue. As a result, many people are turning to gluten-free alternatives to improve their health and well-being.</p>

    <h2>Ingredients for Gluten-Free Cream of Celery Soup</h2>
    <p>Creating a gluten-free cream of celery soup substitute is easier than you might think. Here’s a list of ingredients you’ll need:</p>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Ingredient</th>
                <th>Quantity</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
