    <h2>Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
    <p>Follow these simple steps to make your gluten-free cream of celery soup substitute:</p>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Sauté the Vegetables:</strong> In a large saucepan, melt the butter or heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped celery, onion, and garlic, and sauté until the vegetables are soft and fragrant, about 5-7 minutes.</li>
        <li><strong>Add the Flour:</strong> Sprinkle the gluten-free flour over the sautéed vegetables and stir to coat. Cook for an additional 2 minutes to remove the raw flour taste.</li>
        <li><strong>Incorporate the Broth:</strong> Gradually whisk in the chicken or vegetable broth, ensuring there are no lumps. Bring the mixture to a gentle simmer.</li>
        <li><strong>Add Creaminess:</strong> Stir in the heavy cream or coconut milk, and continue to simmer until the soup thickens, about 5-10 minutes.</li>
        <li><strong>Season:</strong> Add salt and pepper to taste. If desired, you can also add a pinch of thyme or parsley for extra flavor.</li>
        <li><strong>Blend (Optional):</strong> For a smoother consistency, use an immersion blender to puree the soup until it reaches your desired texture.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Nutritional Benefits</h2>
    <p>This gluten-free cream of celery soup substitute is not only delicious but also packed with nutritional benefits. Celery is low in calories and high in fiber, making it a great addition to a healthy diet. It’s also rich in vitamins A, K, and C, as well as antioxidants that help reduce inflammation. By using gluten-free flour and a dairy-free option like coconut milk, this recipe is suitable for a variety of dietary needs.</p>

    <h2>FAQs</h2>
    <div class="faq">
        <h3>Can I use almond milk instead of heavy cream?</h3>
        <p>Yes, almond milk can be used as a substitute for heavy cream, but keep in mind that it will result in a thinner consistency. You may need to adjust the amount of gluten-free flour to achieve the desired thickness.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <h3>How long can I store this soup?</h3>
        <p>This gluten-free cream of celery soup can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. You can also freeze it for up to 3 months. Simply reheat it on the stove or in the microwave before using.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <h3>Can I use this substitute in any recipe that calls for cream of celery soup?</h3>
        <p>Absolutely! This gluten-free substitute can be used in any recipe that calls for cream of celery soup, including casseroles, soups, and stews. It provides the same creamy texture and flavor without the gluten.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>Creating a gluten-free substitute for cream of celery soup is a simple and rewarding process. With just a few basic ingredients, you can enjoy the same rich, creamy texture and flavor in your favorite dishes without worrying about gluten. Whether you’re cooking for yourself or for someone with dietary restrictions, this recipe is a versatile and healthy option that everyone can enjoy. So, the next time a recipe calls for cream of celery soup, give this gluten-free version a try—you won’t be disappointed!</p>

